      <body>
         <entry xml:id="sanqatedron-ys"
            type="mainEntry"
            xml:lang="en"
            prev="#"
            next="#"
            source="Yalkut Shimoni">
            <form type="lemma">
               <orth type="lemma" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" select="true">סנקתדרון</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">snqtdrwn</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic">sanqatedron</pron>
               <gramGrp>
                  <gram type="pos">noun</gram>
                  <gram type="gen">m.</gram>
               </gramGrp>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="sanqatedron-ys-1">
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>assesor</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="grc">
                  <quote>συγκάθεδρος</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>עשרת בניו של המן היו 
                  <app>
                     <lem>סנקתדרין</lem>
                     <rdg wit="#S Ven L">סונקטרין</rdg>
                  </app> של אחשורוש</quote>
                  <bibl>
                     <ref type="witness">Yalq Esth 1057</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">531a: 44</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>The ten sons of Haman were secretaries of Ahasuerus.</quote>
                  </cit>
                  <note>= <bibl type="ancient">Jellineck Bet ha-Midrasch VI (Wien 1877) 57</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">סנקטורים</term>)</note>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>משל למלך שהיה לו סנקליטין ולא היה עושה דבר חוץ מדעתו. [S ר' שמואל בר נחמני אמר במעשה יום ויום נמלך. משל למלך שהיה לו 
                  <app>
                     <lem>סנקליטי'</lem>
                     <rdg wit="#W">סנקתדרין</rdg>
                  </app> ולא היה עושה דבר חוץ מדעתו].</quote>
                  <bibl>
                     <ref type="witness">Yalq 13</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">I 35: 18</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>This may be compared to a king who had two advisors without whose knowledge he did nothing.</quote>
                  </cit>
                  <note>= <bibl type="ancient">GenR 8,3 [I 59: 2]</bibl></note>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>ד"א למלך שהיה לו 
                     <app>
                        <lem>סבקתדרין</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#W S">סנקתדרין</rdg>
                     </app> ולא היה עושה דבר חוץ מדעתו. פעם אחת בקש המלך לעשות דבר חוץ מדעתן, [W S אמר המלך כלום עשיתי אותו סנקתדרין שלי אלא שלא לעשות דבר חוץ מדעתו.]</quote>
                  <bibl>
                     <ref type="witness">Yalq 82</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">I 369: 48</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>R. Shemuʾel ben Naḥman said: It may be compared to a king who had an adviser without whose consent he did not nothing. On one occasion, however, he wished to do something without his consent, whereupon he observed: ‘Surely I made him my adviser for not other reason than that I should do nothing without his consent.” (Freedman / Simon I 422)</quote>
                  </cit>
                  <note>= <bibl type="ancient">GenR 49,2 [II 500 7.8]</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">סנקתדרין</term>, <term xml:lang="jpa">סינקתדרין</term>)</note>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>אמר ליה סבקתדרין דידיה</quote>
                  <bibl>
                     <ref type="witness">Yalq 133</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">II 661: 29</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>Said his adviser to him ...</quote>
                  </cit>
                  <note>= <bibl type="ancient">GenR 78,1 [II 917: 5]</bibl></note>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <note>Cf. GenR. <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">סנקתדרון</ref></note>
